
 * hibernate is a persistence provider for java applications.
 JPA provides interfaces for ORM providers which implements those interfaces.

 * developer has not to be an expert in writing queries,
 can focus only on convenient associations between those,

 * hibernate uses JDBC under the hood to make database calls,

 * If there is one thing that’s often criticized about JPA and Hibernate, it’s that it sometimes execute more queries than you expected,

 * use your logging and statistics components to see if everything works correctly,

 * Fetching only the data you need is a good thing in general,
 but it also requires Hibernate to execute an additional query to initialize each relationship,

 * zapewnij skrypt do tworzenia bazy danych podczas startowania apliakcji,

 * jest to dobra rzecz, gdy baza danych już istnieje i nie trzeba robić,

 * trzeba utworzyć schemat bazy danych własnoręcznie, nie moge
 zrobić tego z pomocą hibernate, bo wszystko spierdole!